1
00:00:16,617 --> 00:00:19,551
[ Miss Parker ]
PEOPLE DON'T JUST SIT AROUND
A JUNKYARD FOR A MONTH.

2
00:00:19,620 --> 00:00:23,555
MR. WOODS SAID HE WAS TIRED
OF BEING ON THE ROAD AND
WANTED SOME PEACE AND QUIET.

3
00:00:23,624 --> 00:00:26,057
HE WANTED TO CATCH UP
ON HIS READING.

4
00:00:26,127 --> 00:00:29,060
LIKE THERE WAS MONEY IN IT.
THAT MAN READ NIGHT AND DAY.

5
00:00:29,130 --> 00:00:31,062
READ?

6
00:00:31,131 --> 00:00:33,431
READ WHAT,
EXACTLY?

7
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:36,101
BOOKS.
HUNDREDS OF 'EM.

8
00:00:37,905 --> 00:00:39,838
LOOK AT ALL THESE.

9
00:00:39,907 --> 00:00:42,541
MR. WOODS BROUGHT
ALL OF THESE WITH HIM?

10
00:00:42,609 --> 00:00:45,210
<i> MOST WERE DELIVERED</i>
<i> WHEN HE BOUGHT OUT STOCK</i>
<i> FROM THE OLD LIBRARY.</i>

11
00:00:45,279 --> 00:00:47,779
ALL OF THESE ARE ABOUT
MATHEMATICS AND SCIENCE.

12
00:00:47,847 --> 00:00:50,849
- SAME HERE.
- MR. WOODS WAS
A BIG SCIENCE NUT.

13
00:00:50,918 --> 00:00:55,520
<i>ONCE, HE SPENT 14 HOURS</i>
<i>SITTING IN THIS ROCKING CHAIR,</i>
<i>FLIPPIN' A HALF-DOLLAR.</i>

14
00:00:55,589 --> 00:00:57,623
FOURTEEN HOURS?

15
00:00:57,691 --> 00:00:59,357
<i> WEIRD, HUH?</i>

16
00:00:59,426 --> 00:01:01,493
SAID HEADS
WERE BETTER ODDS.

17
00:01:01,562 --> 00:01:05,264
<i>SOMETHIN' ABOUT THE SURFACE</i>
<i>AND THE, UH, AERODYNAMICS.</i>

18
00:01:05,332 --> 00:01:09,334
EXCEPT FOR DIMES.
HE SAID NEVER BET WITH A DIME.
DIDN'T SAY WHY.

19
00:01:10,504 --> 00:01:12,136
"FACTORING STATISTICS."

20
00:01:12,205 --> 00:01:15,640
<i>"PHYSICS AND</i>
<i> RANDOM PROBABILITIES."</i>

21
00:01:15,709 --> 00:01:19,211
OH, I THINK I'LL WAIT
FOR THE MOVIE ON THAT EPIC.

22
00:01:20,981 --> 00:01:23,148
<i>"MAKING ODDS EVEN."</i>

23
00:01:23,217 --> 00:01:25,917
MAY I?

24
00:01:28,989 --> 00:01:32,824
<i>JAROD'S LEFT A MESSAGE.</i>
<i>WE'RE CLOSE.</i>

25
00:01:32,893 --> 00:01:35,860
WE'RE NOWHERE EXCEPT
WHERE JAROD WANTS US.

26
00:01:37,398 --> 00:01:39,497
WHY WOULD A MAN
WANT TO LEARN SO MUCH?

27
00:01:39,566 --> 00:01:42,233
DAMN GOOD QUESTION.

28
00:02:07,861 --> 00:02:10,395
- [ Bell Ringing ]
- [ Dealer ] BLACKJACK.

29
00:02:10,464 --> 00:02:13,899
- THE GUY ON TABLE NINE
IS KILLING US.
- ON MY WAY.

30
00:02:13,968 --> 00:02:17,435
- THIS GUY'S GOTTA BE A CHEAT.
- NO, NO. THERE'S NO WAY
HE'S COUNTING EIGHT DECKS.

31
00:02:17,504 --> 00:02:20,906
- [ Dealer ] ANOTHER WINNER!
-<i> [ Cheering, Applauding ]</i>

32
00:02:20,975 --> 00:02:23,909
- HOW MUCH IS HE UP?
- OVER A HUNDRED GRAND,
IT'S GOTTA BE.

33
00:02:23,977 --> 00:02:27,445
<i>-WHAT?</i>
<i>-THE CHIEF, MR. MORGAN, APPROVED</i>
<i> THE INCREASED CREDIT LIMIT.</i>

34
00:02:27,514 --> 00:02:30,148
WHO THE HELL
IS THIS GUY?

35
00:02:32,853 --> 00:02:34,652
[ Cheering,
Applauding Continue ]

36
00:02:34,721 --> 00:02:37,122
IVY, COME HERE.

37
00:02:37,191 --> 00:02:41,159
- WHAT'S HE DRINKING?
- DR. PEPPER.

38
00:02:41,228 --> 00:02:43,895
OFFER CRISTAL OR STOLI.

39
00:02:43,964 --> 00:02:46,431
I TRIED THAT.
HE WANTS DR. PEPPER.

40
00:02:47,735 --> 00:02:49,568
<i>[ Cheering,</i>
<i>  Applauding Continue ]</i>

41
00:02:49,636 --> 00:02:51,470
EXCUSE ME, PLEASE.

42
00:02:51,538 --> 00:02:53,005
DR. PEPPER.

43
00:02:56,210 --> 00:02:58,776
HEADS.

44
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:01,613
- TEN IN A ROW.
- [ Dealer ] ALL BETS ARE DOWN.

45
00:03:03,884 --> 00:03:05,850
BE MY LUCK.

46
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:09,354
MISTER, I COULDN'T EVEN WIN
THE BIG HALF OF A WISHBONE.

47
00:03:13,527 --> 00:03:15,794
HI. I'M IVY.

48
00:03:15,863 --> 00:03:17,929
MR. FELSON.

49
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:22,534
HIT ME.

50
00:03:25,071 --> 00:03:26,605
HOUSE STANDS ON 17.

51
00:03:27,674 --> 00:03:29,641
TWENTY-TWO.
HOUSE WINS.

52
00:03:29,710 --> 00:03:31,643
SEE?
I'M A TOTAL JINX.

53
00:03:31,712 --> 00:03:34,913
YOU CAN ONLY BE A JINX
IF YOU BELIEVE IN LUCK.

54
00:03:34,982 --> 00:03:36,981
DO YOU BELIEVE
IN LUCK?
NO.

55
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:39,985
-<i> [ Dealer ] BLACKJACK.</i>
- ALL RIGHT!

56
00:03:40,054 --> 00:03:42,553
NEITHER DO I.

57
00:03:42,623 --> 00:03:45,690
- AND ANOTHER BLACKJACK.
- [ Cheering,
Applauding Continue ]

58
00:03:45,759 --> 00:03:48,860
THAT'S IT.
I'LL DEAL WITH MR. MORGAN.
SHUT HIM DOWN.

59
00:03:48,929 --> 00:03:51,363
SO MUCH FOR JINX.

60
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:56,468
LET IT RIDE.
<i>[ Cheering, Applauding ]</i>

61
00:03:56,537 --> 00:04:00,038
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>

62
00:04:45,786 --> 00:04:48,720
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>IF HE'S COUNTING CARDS,</i>
<i>I CAN'T CATCH IT.</i>

63
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:51,623
- YOU THINK THIS IS A GAME?
- WELL, THIS IS LAS VEGAS.

64
00:04:51,692 --> 00:04:54,459
- ISN'T EVERYTHING?
-<i> [ Door Opens ]</i>

65
00:04:54,527 --> 00:04:56,728
<i>THIS IS THE GUY,</i>
<i>MR. MORGAN.</i>

66
00:04:58,398 --> 00:05:00,064
LIKE TO COUNT CARDS,
DO YOU?

67
00:05:01,701 --> 00:05:03,868
DAVIS?
HIS NAME
IS JAROD FELSON.

68
00:05:03,937 --> 00:05:06,504
I RAN HIS I.D.--
CRUISE SHIPS TO MONTE CARLO.

69
00:05:06,573 --> 00:05:08,673
DIDN'T FIND A FILE
ON HIM ANYWHERE.

70
00:05:08,742 --> 00:05:12,377
I'M HONORED MR. FELSON HAS
SELECTED THE MARQUIS CASINO...

71
00:05:12,445 --> 00:05:14,378
FOR HIS FIRST SCAM.

72
00:05:14,448 --> 00:05:17,381
WHO HERE THINKS THAT MAKES
MR. FELSON A COMPLETE IDIOT?

73
00:05:17,450 --> 00:05:21,987
<i> [ Jarod ]</i>
<i> MAYBE YOUR SECURITY CHIEF</i>
<i> DIDN'T DIG DEEP ENOUGH.</i>

74
00:05:22,055 --> 00:05:25,022
WHY DON'T YOU TRY
THE F.B.I. FILE UNDER RICO?

75
00:05:26,659 --> 00:05:29,093
YOU RUN RACKETS?

76
00:05:31,465 --> 00:05:34,131
<i> [ Typing On Keyboard ]</i>

77
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:36,400
HELLO, MR. MORGAN!

78
00:05:37,771 --> 00:05:40,738
YOU SET THIS UP.
YOU KNEW WE'D HAVE
THIS CONVERSATION.

79
00:05:40,807 --> 00:05:42,874
NOT BAD
FOR A COMPLETE IDIOT.

80
00:05:42,943 --> 00:05:44,609
<i>[ Davis ]</i>
<i>WHERE ARE YOUR</i>
<i>BLACKJACK WINNINGS?</i>

81
00:05:44,678 --> 00:05:49,680
I HAD THEM DELIVERED
TO MR. MORGAN'S OFFICE
BY A NICE YOUNG LADY NAMED IVY.

82
00:05:49,749 --> 00:05:53,017
- YOU'RE GIVING ME
THE MONEY BACK?
- MONEY DOESN'T INTEREST ME.

83
00:05:53,086 --> 00:05:55,019
IF NOT MONEY,
WHAT DOES INTEREST YOU?

84
00:05:55,088 --> 00:05:58,356
I'M NOT HERE TO MAKE
A FOOL OF YOU, MR. MORGAN,
OR TO RIP YOU OFF.

85
00:05:58,425 --> 00:05:59,925
SO, WHAT DO YOU WANT?

86
00:05:59,993 --> 00:06:02,260
EXCUSE ME?

87
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:07,032
<i>YOU HAVE AN INCREDIBLE</i>
<i>SECURITY SYSTEM, MR. MORGAN.</i>

88
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:09,534
IT'S A SHAME NO ONE HERE
KNOWS HOW TO USE IT.

89
00:06:09,602 --> 00:06:13,705
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>THE BET WAS $1,000.</i>
<i>WHAT DID THE DEALER PAY OUT?</i>

90
00:06:13,774 --> 00:06:16,274
PURPLE CHIP.
A GRAND.

91
00:06:16,342 --> 00:06:18,276
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>MEET MARTIN RAWLINGS.</i>

92
00:06:18,345 --> 00:06:20,645
<i>HE'S BEEN DEALING BLACKJACK HERE</i>
<i>FOR 10 YEARS.</i>

93
00:06:20,714 --> 00:06:23,748
HE'S THE BEST WE HAVE.
THAT'S TOO BAD, BECAUSE
HE'S ABOUT TO LOSE HIS JOB.

94
00:06:23,816 --> 00:06:26,951
<i>HE USED TO WORK</i>
<i>AT A MAGIC CLUB IN KENTUCKY.</i>

95
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:29,954
<i>HIS SPECIALTY?</i>
<i>SLEIGHT-OF-HAND.</i>

96
00:06:30,023 --> 00:06:33,624
<i>AN EXTRA THOUSAND FOR THE PLANT.</i>
<i>HE PASSES IT TO THE COURIER.</i>

97
00:06:33,693 --> 00:06:36,661
GAVE THE CHIP TO THE WAITRESS.
WHERE'S SHE GOING?

98
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:39,664
FORGET THE COURIER.
FOCUS ON THE CHIP.

99
00:06:39,733 --> 00:06:41,766
BECAUSE IT
AND DOZENS LIKE IT...

100
00:06:41,835 --> 00:06:44,569
ARE ON THEIR WAY
TO YOUR SECURITY CHIEF'S
MACE HOLSTER.

101
00:06:44,637 --> 00:06:46,604
MR. MORGAN--
<i>[ Morgan ]</i>
<i>REMOVE IT.</i>

102
00:06:46,673 --> 00:06:48,507
I'VE WORKED HERE
FOR TEN YEARS.

103
00:06:48,575 --> 00:06:51,743
- ALL OF A SUDDEN SOME JERK
IN A SHINY SUIT--
- HELP HIM.

104
00:07:02,589 --> 00:07:04,689
THAT'S OVER $10,000.

105
00:07:07,227 --> 00:07:09,260
GET HIM OUTTA HERE.

106
00:07:11,497 --> 00:07:13,431
IT'S NOT GONNA STOP HERE.

107
00:07:13,499 --> 00:07:16,835
A CASINO-- IT'S ALWAYS A TARGET.
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

108
00:07:18,238 --> 00:07:20,171
SO, MR. FELSON,

109
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:22,173
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

110
00:07:22,242 --> 00:07:25,843
FIVE PERCENT
OF WHAT YOU<i> DON'T</i> LOSE
WHILE I'M IN CHARGE.

111
00:07:31,384 --> 00:07:34,619
DON'T YOU LITTLE LADIES FORGET--
COME SEE MY SHOW TONIGHT.

112
00:07:34,688 --> 00:07:38,656
THERE'S NO COVER, NO MINIMUM,
AND THERE'S FREE
<i>HOT</i> HORS D'OEUVRES.

113
00:07:38,725 --> 00:07:41,892
[ Ladies Giggling ]
I'LL SEE Y'ALL LATER.
BYE-BYE.

114
00:07:43,597 --> 00:07:45,330
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

115
00:07:45,399 --> 00:07:47,331
HEY THERE, TEDDY BEAR.

116
00:07:47,401 --> 00:07:50,668
YOU COME TO RUB ELBOWS
WITH THE KING OF ROCK AND ROLL?

117
00:07:50,737 --> 00:07:53,170
NO. I'M TRYING
TO UNDERSTAND THIS.

118
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:57,308
YOU DRESS UP IN A RENTED COSTUME
AND PRETEND TO BE A DEAD SINGER?

119
00:07:58,578 --> 00:08:02,514
"SINGER"?
SON, DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHO I AM?

120
00:08:02,583 --> 00:08:05,817
- WELL, ACTUALLY, I WOULD ASSU--
- YOU ARE LOOKING
AT A NATIONAL MONUMENT.

121
00:08:05,885 --> 00:08:08,486
MOUNT RUSHMORE
IN BLUE SUEDE SHOES.

122
00:08:08,555 --> 00:08:10,889
<i>THERE'S NOT A HUMAN BEING</i>
<i>ON GOD'S GREEN EARTH...</i>

123
00:08:10,957 --> 00:08:13,891
THAT HAS EVER DEMANDED
THE ATTENTION AND RESPECT...

124
00:08:13,961 --> 00:08:16,561
OF THE MAN
YOU ARE LOOKIN' AT
THIS VERY MOMENT.

125
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:19,931
HEY, BERNIE, SOME GUY AT THE
CRAPS TABLE SAYS HE'LL GIVE YOU
FIVE BUCKS TO GOOSE HIS WIFE.

126
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,432
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

127
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:24,668
WELL, MY FANS BECKON.
I MUST GO.

128
00:08:26,673 --> 00:08:28,673
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

129
00:08:34,214 --> 00:08:36,247
THAT IS THE LAST OF THEM.

130
00:08:36,316 --> 00:08:39,250
I'VE RUN EVERY ONE OF THESE
THROUGH THE MAINFRAME,

131
00:08:39,319 --> 00:08:41,686
AND I CAN STILL FIND
NO CORRELATION.

132
00:08:41,754 --> 00:08:44,756
ALTHOUGH THERE IS SOMETHING
TO BE SAID FOR JAROD'S THEORY...

133
00:08:44,824 --> 00:08:48,526
<i>ON THE AERODYNAMICS</i>
<i>OF A 50-CENT PIECE.</i>

134
00:08:50,430 --> 00:08:52,530
HEADS.

135
00:08:52,599 --> 00:08:54,298
OKAY.

136
00:08:57,371 --> 00:09:00,505
JAROD IS TRYING
TO TELL ME SOMETHING,

137
00:09:00,574 --> 00:09:03,140
AND THIS BOOK IS THE CLUE.

138
00:09:04,477 --> 00:09:06,411
THAT'S A HELL OF A CLUE, SYD.

139
00:09:06,479 --> 00:09:08,947
JAROD HIGHLIGHTED
THE ENTIRE BOOK.

140
00:09:09,016 --> 00:09:11,316
<i>BUT LOOK AT</i>
<i>THIS PAGE OF STATISTICS.</i>

141
00:09:11,385 --> 00:09:13,718
HE TRACED OVER
ALL THE NUMBER EIGHTS.

142
00:09:14,988 --> 00:09:18,556
<i> NOW, EIGHT</i>
<i> IS JAROD'S FAVORITE NUMBER.</i>

143
00:09:18,625 --> 00:09:20,892
HIS FAVORITE FIGURE.

144
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,894
HE CALLS IT
UPRIGHT INFINITY...

145
00:09:22,962 --> 00:09:28,199
BECAUSE OF THE WAY ONE LOOP
COILS INTO THE NEXT,
NEVER ENDING.

146
00:09:28,268 --> 00:09:31,469
MAYBE YOUR BOY WONDER
HAS TURNED INTO BRIAN BOITANO.

147
00:09:33,806 --> 00:09:35,740
MM-MMM.

148
00:09:35,809 --> 00:09:37,676
<i> JAROD IS LOOKING</i>
<i> FOR A PURPOSE.</i>

149
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:39,610
HE'S PLAYING GAMES.

150
00:09:39,679 --> 00:09:41,445
GAMES?

151
00:09:41,514 --> 00:09:43,447
<i> GAMES WITH NUMBERS?</i>

152
00:09:43,517 --> 00:09:46,183
<i> HIGH-STAKES GAMES?</i>
<i> HIGH-STAKES POKER.</i>

153
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:48,853
BACCARAT.

154
00:09:49,856 --> 00:09:51,790
WELL, THAT NARROWS IT DOWN...

155
00:09:51,858 --> 00:09:55,293
TO ANY OF THE THOUSANDS
OF GAMING ESTABLISHMENTS
ON THE PLANET.

156
00:09:55,362 --> 00:09:57,695
ANY IDEAS WHERE TO START?

157
00:10:05,872 --> 00:10:08,873
I KNOW
JUST THE MAN TO SEE.

158
00:10:18,184 --> 00:10:19,817
HELLO.

159
00:10:19,886 --> 00:10:21,485
HAVE YOU READ THIS?

160
00:10:21,554 --> 00:10:23,721
IT'S-- IT'S VERY GOOD.

161
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:26,157
IT'S ABOUT THIS INQUISITIVE
LITTLE MONKEY NAMED GEORGE.

162
00:10:26,225 --> 00:10:28,058
HE WAS<i> CURIOUS.</i>

163
00:10:28,127 --> 00:10:31,462
<i>I'VE ONLY READ IT</i>
<i>ABOUT A THOUSAND TIMES.</i>

164
00:10:31,531 --> 00:10:34,465
OH, WELL, GOOD.
THEN MAYBE YOU CAN HELP ME.

165
00:10:34,534 --> 00:10:36,734
WHO IS THE MAN
IN THE YELLOW HAT?

166
00:10:37,904 --> 00:10:39,837
I DON'T KNOW.

167
00:10:39,906 --> 00:10:41,906
OH, WELL.
THANK YOU ANYWAY.
OKAY!

168
00:10:45,345 --> 00:10:47,345
CAN I HELP YOU?

169
00:10:53,085 --> 00:10:55,720
JAROD.
IT'S ABOUT TIME.

170
00:10:55,789 --> 00:10:58,723
HANLON'S
BEEN ASKING FOR YOU.
ASKING FOR ME?

171
00:10:58,792 --> 00:11:03,061
EXPOSING DAVIS'S SCAM
SAVED HIM MORE MONEY THAN HIS
CREATIVE ACCOUNTANT EVER DID.

172
00:11:04,263 --> 00:11:06,897
STEVE HANLON,
JAROD FELSON.

173
00:11:06,966 --> 00:11:08,833
IT'S A PLEASURE
TO MEET YOU, SIR.

174
00:11:08,901 --> 00:11:11,335
I WANT TO THANK YOU
FOR HELPING US OUT.

175
00:11:11,405 --> 00:11:14,872
<i>HERE AT THE MARQUIS,</i>
<i>WE THINK OF OURSELVES AS FAMILY.</i>

176
00:11:14,941 --> 00:11:17,876
NOTHING WORSE THAN BEING
BETRAYED BY THOSE CLOSE TO YOU.

177
00:11:17,944 --> 00:11:20,678
<i>TRULY IMPRESSIVE, THE WAY</i>
<i>YOU CAME IN AND CLEANED HOUSE.</i>

178
00:11:20,747 --> 00:11:24,048
<i>I GUESS THE ONLY QUESTION</i>
<i> I HAVE... IS WHY?</i>

179
00:11:24,116 --> 00:11:26,617
<i>WHY WOULD A MAN</i>
<i>I NEVER HEARD OF,</i>
<i>NEVER LAID EYES ON...</i>

180
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:29,921
STEP IN TO HELP MY BUSINESS
OUT OF THE BLUE LIKE THAT?

181
00:11:31,991 --> 00:11:33,925
I'M A FAN, MR. HANLON.

182
00:11:33,993 --> 00:11:37,361
<i>YOU TOOK A NO-NAME VIDEO STORE.</i>
<i> YOU TURNED IT INTO AN EMPIRE.</i>

183
00:11:37,430 --> 00:11:40,931
YOU LISTEN TO PEOPLE.
YOU GIVE THEM WHAT
THEY WANT. I LIKE THAT.

184
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,267
YOU STUDY PEOPLE TOO.

185
00:11:43,336 --> 00:11:45,102
MASTER YOUR SPACE.

186
00:11:45,171 --> 00:11:47,305
MY LECTURE AT BROWNSTONE.

187
00:11:47,374 --> 00:11:50,274
- THAT MUST HAVE BEEN
12 YEARS AGO.
-<i> IT WAS 11.</i>

188
00:11:50,343 --> 00:11:54,412
AND IT WAS THE FIRST TIME
YOU USED "FAMILY FIRST"
AS THE COMPANY MOTTO.

189
00:11:54,481 --> 00:11:56,380
<i>YOU WERE THERE?</i>
<i> NO, SIR.</i>

190
00:11:56,449 --> 00:11:59,317
BUT I BOUGHT THE CASSETTE.
I WORE OUT MY TAPE PLAYER.

191
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:02,553
<i>PETER, WATCH OUT.</i>
<i>I MIGHT STEAL THIS MAN</i>
<i>FOR CORPORATE.</i>

192
00:12:02,622 --> 00:12:04,288
[ Laughs ]
WELL, THANK YOU, SIR.

193
00:12:04,357 --> 00:12:06,390
WE FINALLY GOT CORRUPTION
OUT OF THE MARQUIS.

194
00:12:06,459 --> 00:12:08,393
I WOULD LIKE TO HELP
KEEP IT THAT WAY.

195
00:12:08,461 --> 00:12:12,129
JAROD, YOU HAVE MY PERMISSION
TO DO WHATEVER IT TAKES.

196
00:12:12,198 --> 00:12:14,732
I THANK YOU, SIR.

197
00:12:14,801 --> 00:12:16,734
JAROD,
THIS IS MY WIFE, KITTY.

198
00:12:16,803 --> 00:12:20,638
KITTY, JAROD FELSON,
OUR NEW SECURITY CHIEF.

199
00:12:20,707 --> 00:12:22,907
<i> NICE TO MEET YOU.</i>
A PLEASURE, MR. FELSON.

200
00:12:22,976 --> 00:12:25,643
I SAW YOUR PICTURE
IN THE LOBBY.

201
00:12:25,712 --> 00:12:27,645
KITTY USED TO
HEADLINE THE SHOW HERE.

202
00:12:27,714 --> 00:12:30,848
UH, I NEED TO STEAL
MR. HANLON FOR A MOMENT.

203
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:33,784
- NICE TO MEET YOU, MR. FELSON.
- NICE TO MEET YOU.

204
00:12:36,222 --> 00:12:38,823
SO, YOU'RE A COMPANY MAN, HUH?

205
00:12:38,892 --> 00:12:42,593
I AGREE WITH MR. HANLON'S
THEORIES ON FAMILY,
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU MEAN.

206
00:12:42,662 --> 00:12:46,397
THE ONLY THING
HANLON LIKES ABOUT FAMILY
IS THE PROCREATING PART.

207
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:50,601
HE SPENDS MILLIONS
BUILDING THIS PLAYGROUND...

208
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:53,604
AND PROCLAIMS FAMILIES NOW HAVE
A REASON TO VACATION TOGETHER.

209
00:12:53,673 --> 00:12:56,407
AND YOU DON'T THINK
THEY DO?

210
00:12:56,476 --> 00:12:58,409
AT A CASINO?

211
00:12:58,478 --> 00:13:03,347
JAROD, PEOPLE WHO NEVER EVEN
DREAMED OF GAMBLING NOW THINK
IT'S SANCTIONED BY GOD.

212
00:13:03,416 --> 00:13:06,818
ADD A FEW FLASHY ARCADES,
EVEN THE DAMN KIDS
GO HOME BROKE.

213
00:13:09,055 --> 00:13:11,221
DON'T LET HANLON FOOL YOU.

214
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:13,791
HE MAY TALK
THE NEW CORPORATE ATTITUDE
IN THIS TOWN--

215
00:13:13,859 --> 00:13:17,027
DEEP DOWN,
HE'S STILL OLD VEGAS.

216
00:13:59,372 --> 00:14:01,305
[ Monitor Beeping ]

217
00:14:02,609 --> 00:14:05,609
I'M SORRY IT TOOK ME
SO LONG TO GET HERE, MAGGIE.

218
00:14:16,589 --> 00:14:19,090
<i> [ Beeping Continues ]</i>

219
00:14:26,699 --> 00:14:28,633
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>

220
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:31,201
<i> VISITING HOURS</i>
<i> ARE OVER AT 8:00.</i>

221
00:14:31,271 --> 00:14:33,504
<i> [ Woman On P.A. ]</i>
<i> DR. RYAN TO O.R.</i>

222
00:14:33,573 --> 00:14:36,507
I THOUGHT
SHE WAS ALL ALONE.

223
00:14:36,576 --> 00:14:38,576
WELL...

224
00:14:39,712 --> 00:14:41,712
SHE'S NOT ALONE
ANYMORE.

225
00:14:42,815 --> 00:14:44,915
<i>NO OFFENSE, UH--</i>

226
00:14:44,984 --> 00:14:47,518
SHE ISN'T GOING
TO WAKE UP.

227
00:14:48,821 --> 00:14:52,390
I KNOW.
BUT IT DOESN'T MEAN
SHE CAN'T HEAR ME.

228
00:14:53,994 --> 00:14:55,993
MY NAME'S JAROD.

229
00:14:57,797 --> 00:14:59,730
OH.

230
00:14:59,799 --> 00:15:01,966
NAME'S BUDDY.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

231
00:15:05,637 --> 00:15:09,539
IF-IF ANYTHING
HAPPENS TO HER,
WILL YOU PAGE ME?

232
00:15:11,477 --> 00:15:13,777
I DIDN'T MEAN TO...

233
00:15:13,846 --> 00:15:16,347
SOUND COLD BEFORE, BUT...

234
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:20,451
I'VE LEARNED NOT TO
GET TOO ATTACHED.

235
00:15:21,854 --> 00:15:24,388
BUT IT IS NICE TO KNOW...

236
00:15:24,457 --> 00:15:26,456
SOMEONE GIVES A DAMN.

237
00:15:31,196 --> 00:15:33,196
<i>[ Door Closes ]</i>

238
00:15:44,644 --> 00:15:47,478
[ Tires Screeching ]

239
00:15:47,547 --> 00:15:49,746
MISS PARKER,
WHAT ARE WE DOING HERE?

240
00:15:49,815 --> 00:15:51,748
SAYING HELLO
TO AN OLD FRIEND.

241
00:15:51,818 --> 00:15:56,219
HEY, I KNOW YOU'RE EXCITED
TO SEE ME. JUST KEEP IT
IN YOUR PANTS, VITO.

242
00:15:56,289 --> 00:15:58,822
SYDNEY,
SAY HELLO TO JOHNNY.

243
00:15:58,890 --> 00:16:01,091
JOHNNY'S BROTHER
HACKED INTO
THE COMPUTER PROFILES...

244
00:16:01,159 --> 00:16:03,326
AT ONE OF OUR
SATELLITE COMPANIES
IN CHICAGO.

245
00:16:03,395 --> 00:16:07,264
<i> NOW HE'S SERVING</i>
<i> 10 HARD IN JOLIET.</i>
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

246
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:11,101
<i> HE'S WORKING A CON</i>
<i> IN A CASINO.</i>

247
00:16:11,170 --> 00:16:14,338
THIS FACE?
HE'S NOT A CON.
HE'S NOT THE TYPE.

248
00:16:14,407 --> 00:16:16,506
HE IS<i> EVERY</i> TYPE.

249
00:16:16,575 --> 00:16:18,308
<i> FIND HIM FOR ME.</i>

250
00:16:19,912 --> 00:16:22,846
PASS.
MMM.
NOT AN OPTION.

251
00:16:22,915 --> 00:16:25,849
BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,
I HEARD THAT
AT 3:00 TOMORROW,

252
00:16:25,918 --> 00:16:29,986
YOU'RE SHIPPING OUT
A BOATLOAD OF-- [ Whispering ]
STOLEN CARS TO VENEZUELA.

253
00:16:30,055 --> 00:16:33,957
NOW, IF YOU DON'T WANT
THE PORT AUTHORITY ALL OVER
YOUR LITTLE BOAT, WELL--

254
00:16:34,026 --> 00:16:36,593
YOU WOULDN'T.
WANNA BET?

255
00:16:37,730 --> 00:16:39,663
FIFTY THOUSAND
FOR INFORMATION.

256
00:16:39,732 --> 00:16:41,732
NO QUESTIONS ASKED.

257
00:16:45,671 --> 00:16:48,005
<i> [ Applause ]</i>
[ Sighs ]

258
00:16:48,073 --> 00:16:50,006
<i>[ Emcee ]</i>
<i>THANKS, LADIES AND GENTLEMEN.</i>

259
00:16:50,076 --> 00:16:52,208
<i>YOU'VE BEEN</i>
<i>A TERRIFIC AUDIENCE TONIGHT.</i>

260
00:16:52,278 --> 00:16:54,210
HEY.

261
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:57,381
<i>IF YOU'RE NOT STAYING</i>
<i>AT OUR FABULOUS HOTEL,</i>
<i>PLEASE DRIVE SAFELY.</i>

262
00:16:57,449 --> 00:16:59,416
<i> WELL, WELCOME</i>
<i> TO THE HEARTBREAK HOTEL.</i>

263
00:16:59,485 --> 00:17:02,352
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
YOU SHOULD BE ON STAGE.

264
00:17:02,421 --> 00:17:05,656
OH, NO.
THERE'S NO MORE STAGE
FOR THE KING.

265
00:17:05,725 --> 00:17:07,558
THE CASINO FIRED ME.

266
00:17:07,627 --> 00:17:09,559
I'M SORRY.

267
00:17:09,629 --> 00:17:12,463
DID IT HAVE SOMETHING TO DO
WITH THAT BIRD THING?

268
00:17:13,799 --> 00:17:16,467
- BIRD THING?
- THE... GOOSE.

269
00:17:16,535 --> 00:17:18,535
[ Snickers ]

270
00:17:18,603 --> 00:17:22,973
NO. NO, THEY SAID
THEY HAD HAD COMPLAINTS
ABOUT THE SHOW.

271
00:17:23,041 --> 00:17:25,910
<i> SO I PUT ON</i>
<i> 20, 30 POUNDS.</i>

272
00:17:25,978 --> 00:17:28,245
YOU THINK IT'S EASY
BEING THE IDOL OF MILLIONS?

273
00:17:28,314 --> 00:17:31,214
I WOULD GUESS NO.
<i> YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT IT ISN'T.</i>

274
00:17:31,283 --> 00:17:34,518
I SACRIFICED EVERYTHING.
I DID IT 'CAUSE I LOVED IT.

275
00:17:34,587 --> 00:17:36,520
IT'S WHAT
THE PEOPLE WANTED.

276
00:17:36,588 --> 00:17:40,523
<i> I JUST WISH SOME OF</i>
<i> THOSE CASINO BIGWIGS</i>
<i> COULD SPEND ONE HOUR...</i>

277
00:17:40,592 --> 00:17:42,960
WEARING THE CAPE--
JUST ONE HOUR.

278
00:17:43,028 --> 00:17:47,097
THEY'D WALK AWAY
SINGING A DIFFERENT TUNE,
I GUARAN-DAMN-TEE YOU.

279
00:17:47,166 --> 00:17:50,267
WELL, COULDN'T YOU GET A JOB
AT ANOTHER CASINO?

280
00:17:50,336 --> 00:17:53,170
NO. NO, BUDDY BOY.

281
00:17:53,239 --> 00:17:57,941
AFTER 24 YEARS
OF MAKING PEOPLE SMILE,

282
00:17:58,010 --> 00:18:00,009
SINGING THE SONGS AND...

283
00:18:02,281 --> 00:18:04,214
SPREADING
THE GOOD VIBRATIONS,

284
00:18:04,283 --> 00:18:06,883
I'M AFRAID IT'S
THE END OF THE LINE
FOR THE KING.

285
00:18:08,620 --> 00:18:12,556
<i> NO, WE-- WE HAD</i>
<i> ONE HELL OF A RIDE THOUGH.</i>
<i> DIDN'T WE?</i>

286
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:15,626
I BET YOU DID.

287
00:18:15,694 --> 00:18:17,627
LOOK, I-- I'M SORRY.

288
00:18:17,697 --> 00:18:20,630
I'M SPILLING MY GUTS,
AND I DON'T EVEN
KNOW YOUR NAME.

289
00:18:20,699 --> 00:18:22,699
JAROD.

290
00:18:22,767 --> 00:18:24,701
<i>FELSON.</i>

291
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:26,604
BERNIE BAXLEY.

292
00:18:26,672 --> 00:18:29,406
WELL, IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU,
BERNIE BAXLEY.

293
00:18:29,475 --> 00:18:31,475
THANKS.

294
00:18:32,878 --> 00:18:34,878
JAROD?

295
00:18:37,182 --> 00:18:39,115
I'M SCARED.

296
00:18:39,184 --> 00:18:41,618
OF WHAT?

297
00:18:41,687 --> 00:18:43,687
HIM.

298
00:18:59,504 --> 00:19:00,571
<i>[ Phone Rings ]</i>

299
00:19:03,509 --> 00:19:06,076
- SYDNEY.
- HELLO, SYDNEY.

300
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:09,012
<i> JAROD.</i>
<i> GOOD TO HEAR FROM YOU.</i>

301
00:19:09,081 --> 00:19:10,914
IT'S BEEN A WHILE.

302
00:19:10,982 --> 00:19:12,916
WHERE ARE YOU CALLING FROM?

303
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:15,251
YOU'LL FIGURE THAT OUT
SOONER OR LATER.

304
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:19,656
- I'M COUNTING ON LATER.
- COUNTING ON OR<i> BETTING</i> ON?

305
00:19:19,725 --> 00:19:21,658
YOU ARE SO WELL READ.

306
00:19:21,727 --> 00:19:26,162
YOU KNOW, IT'S SUCH A PLEASURE
TO HAVE THE FREEDOM TO READ
WHATEVER I WANT THESE DAYS.

307
00:19:26,231 --> 00:19:28,465
WHY THE GAMES, JAROD?

308
00:19:28,534 --> 00:19:31,000
IT'S IN THE MAIL.

309
00:19:31,069 --> 00:19:33,002
JAROD?

310
00:19:33,072 --> 00:19:35,639
[ Dial Tone ]

311
00:19:35,708 --> 00:19:38,208
[ Imitating Monkey Hooting ]

312
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:05,668
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I'M HAVING TROUBLE UNDERSTANDING</i>
<i>THE ACCOUNT TOTALS FROM JULY.</i>

313
00:20:05,738 --> 00:20:08,171
GUY EVEN WORKS
ON HIS DAY OFF.

314
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:10,173
YOU PAY ME
TO LOCATE DISCREPANCIES,

315
00:20:10,242 --> 00:20:13,176
AND I CAN'T RECONCILE
THE FIGURES AGAINST LAST YEAR,

316
00:20:13,245 --> 00:20:15,479
SPECIFICALLY JULY.

317
00:20:17,817 --> 00:20:21,685
- JUST SET IT ASIDE.
- SET IT ASIDE?

318
00:20:21,754 --> 00:20:24,821
JAROD, THERE'S A REASON
THOSE NUMBERS DON'T MATCH.

319
00:20:29,561 --> 00:20:32,495
ONE OF OUR SHOWGIRLS
WAS ATTACKED
IN THE PARKING GARAGE.

320
00:20:32,564 --> 00:20:37,600
OUR REVENUE DROPPED 30%
FOR THREE DAYS.
IT WAS AN ANOMALY.

321
00:20:37,670 --> 00:20:40,070
<i> [ Morgan ]</i>
<i> NOT TO MENTION</i>
<i> A PUBLICITY NIGHTMARE.</i>

322
00:20:40,139 --> 00:20:44,341
FORTUNATELY,
THE MEGABUSTER JACKPOT
HIT TWO DAYS LATER...

323
00:20:44,410 --> 00:20:47,110
<i> AND EVERYBODY</i>
<i> CAME BACK.</i>

324
00:20:47,179 --> 00:20:51,581
SOMETIMES LADY LUCK
EVEN SMILES ON THE HOUSE.

325
00:20:51,650 --> 00:20:54,217
<i> [ Hanlon Chuckling ]</i>

326
00:20:57,289 --> 00:20:59,389
<i>[ Ivy ]</i>
<i>THANKS FOR THE ESCORT,</i>
<i>MR. FELSON.</i>

327
00:20:59,458 --> 00:21:03,327
NONE OF US
WALK ALONE ANYMORE.
NOT SINCE MAGGIE.

328
00:21:03,395 --> 00:21:06,330
MAGGIE.
SHE WAS THE WOMAN
THAT WAS ATTACKED.

329
00:21:06,398 --> 00:21:08,332
RIGHT.
YOU KNEW HER?

330
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,435
WELL, I'D SEEN HER
IN THE SHOW AND AROUND--
BACKSTAGE, YOU KNOW.

331
00:21:11,503 --> 00:21:14,437
I READ IN THE PAPER
THERE WAS NO EVIDENCE
OF A ROBBERY.

332
00:21:14,506 --> 00:21:16,439
NO.

333
00:21:16,509 --> 00:21:19,442
THE NIGHT IT HAPPENED,
THE SHOWROOM
WAS COMPLETELY PACKED.

334
00:21:19,512 --> 00:21:21,444
IT WAS
THE FOURTH OF JULY.

335
00:21:21,514 --> 00:21:23,446
MAGGIE
WAS SO HAPPY.

336
00:21:23,516 --> 00:21:26,449
SHE'D JUST LANDED
THE LEAD IN A BIG SHOW
IN ATLANTIC CITY.

337
00:21:26,519 --> 00:21:28,451
MAGGIE WAS LEAVING TOWN?

338
00:21:28,521 --> 00:21:30,453
YEAH, I GUESS SO.

339
00:21:30,523 --> 00:21:32,523
I KNOW I WOULD.

340
00:21:34,126 --> 00:21:36,293
GOD, IT HAPPENED
RIGHT HERE.

341
00:21:39,198 --> 00:21:42,932
- GARDENIAS.
- EXCUSE ME?

342
00:21:44,203 --> 00:21:47,637
UH, MAGGIE ALWAYS WORE
A GARDENIA IN HER HAIR.

343
00:21:47,706 --> 00:21:50,106
<i>I KNOW IT SOUNDS STRANGE,</i>
<i>BUT...</i>

344
00:21:50,175 --> 00:21:54,177
EVERY TIME I PASS THIS SPOT,
I SWEAR I CAN SMELL GARDENIAS.

345
00:21:56,314 --> 00:21:58,648
LISTEN, THANKS.
SURE.

346
00:22:01,787 --> 00:22:04,087
DRIVE SAFE.
THANK YOU.

347
00:22:06,192 --> 00:22:08,358
[ Engine Starts ]

348
00:23:43,655 --> 00:23:46,023
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>
<i>THIS IS WEIRD, SYDNEY.</i>

349
00:23:47,392 --> 00:23:49,392
<i>THIS DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.</i>

350
00:23:57,803 --> 00:23:59,970
I MADE IT INSIDE.

351
00:24:00,038 --> 00:24:01,904
SHE DOESN'T HEAR ME.

352
00:24:01,973 --> 00:24:04,640
<i>THE HALLWAY'S DARK.</i>

353
00:24:04,709 --> 00:24:06,710
<i>IT SMELLS LIKE...</i>

354
00:24:08,546 --> 00:24:10,546
FLOWERS.

355
00:24:14,753 --> 00:24:16,753
I ROUND A CORNER.

356
00:24:19,457 --> 00:24:21,491
TO WHERE?

357
00:24:24,830 --> 00:24:26,830
THE KITCHEN.

358
00:24:29,134 --> 00:24:31,134
I'M GETTING CLOSER.

359
00:24:32,705 --> 00:24:35,838
I KNOW THEY MADE HER
DO THINGS THAT SHE
DIDN'T WANT TO DO.

360
00:24:39,911 --> 00:24:42,112
DID SHE DO SOMETHING WRONG?

361
00:24:42,180 --> 00:24:47,350
KEEP GOING, JAROD.
NOW FOCUS ON THE KILLER
AND NOT THE VICTIM.

362
00:24:57,762 --> 00:25:00,664
IS THE WOMAN ON THE BED
HER OLD SELF
OR HER NEW SELF?

363
00:25:00,732 --> 00:25:02,933
THEY ARE THE SAME PERSON.

364
00:25:03,002 --> 00:25:04,634
SHE DOESN'T THINK SO.

365
00:25:04,703 --> 00:25:08,071
[ Sydney ]
YOU HAVE WHAT YOU NEED
TO COMPLETE THE SIMULATION.

366
00:25:08,139 --> 00:25:11,074
[ Young Jarod ]
BUT I DON'T KNOW WHY HE'S THERE.

367
00:25:11,142 --> 00:25:13,877
IS HE TRYING TO KILL NORMA JEAN
OR MARILYN?

368
00:25:13,946 --> 00:25:16,646
I'M CONFUSED.

369
00:25:16,715 --> 00:25:19,516
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>FINISH THE SIMULATION.</i>

370
00:25:19,585 --> 00:25:22,052
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>
<i>IT JUST SEEMS SO UNFAIR.</i>

371
00:25:23,788 --> 00:25:26,289
NO ONE
SHOULD HAVE TO DIE ALONE.

372
00:25:29,494 --> 00:25:31,995
SOMETHING'S WRONG
WITH THIS PICTURE.

373
00:25:41,006 --> 00:25:44,007
SOMETHING'S WRONG
WITH THIS PICTURE TOO,
SYDNEY.

374
00:26:37,162 --> 00:26:39,763
SOMEBODY'S LUCK
JUST RAN OUT.

375
00:26:43,368 --> 00:26:45,301
[ Bell Dings ]

376
00:26:45,370 --> 00:26:48,304
THANKS FOR THE ESCORT,
MR. FELSON.
IT WAS MY PLEASURE.

377
00:26:48,373 --> 00:26:53,309
NOW, YOU'RE ABSOLUTELY SURE
THAT YOU DON'T KNOW WHO THIS
MAN IN THE YELLOW HAT WAS?

378
00:26:53,378 --> 00:26:55,311
SORRY.

379
00:26:55,380 --> 00:26:58,314
MY CAR'S RIGHT HERE.
WELL,
HAVE A GOOD NIGHT.

380
00:26:58,383 --> 00:27:00,383
THANKS.

381
00:27:08,026 --> 00:27:10,026
THIS WAS JUST DELIVERED.

382
00:27:25,177 --> 00:27:27,177
COME ON, SYDNEY.

383
00:27:31,749 --> 00:27:34,083
WE HAVE
A PLANE TO CATCH.

384
00:27:46,531 --> 00:27:48,531
PACKIN' UP, HUH?

385
00:27:50,034 --> 00:27:52,835
GOTTA STAY MOBILE, SON.

386
00:27:52,904 --> 00:27:55,838
YOU KNOW, I WAS THINKIN'
ABOUT HEADIN' BACK EAST.

387
00:27:55,907 --> 00:27:58,007
YOU KNOW, TRY BRANSON.

388
00:27:58,076 --> 00:28:00,209
VEGAS HAS CHANGED,
YOU KNOW.

389
00:28:00,278 --> 00:28:04,447
NOT MUCH
IN A CITY LIKE THIS
FOR AN OLD DOG LIKE ME.

390
00:28:04,515 --> 00:28:06,515
THANKS.

391
00:28:10,956 --> 00:28:14,157
OH,<i> THAT...</i>

392
00:28:14,225 --> 00:28:16,392
IS AN OFFICIAL PIECE...

393
00:28:16,461 --> 00:28:18,461
OF GRACELAND
MEMORABILIA.

394
00:28:18,530 --> 00:28:20,463
WELL,
IT'S VERY NICE.
[ Sighs ]

395
00:28:20,531 --> 00:28:23,466
OH, KID, YOU KNOW,

396
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:25,969
YOU SHOULD SEE THE HOUSE
IN PERSON.

397
00:28:26,038 --> 00:28:29,639
IT'S, UH-- THE KING
NAMED IT FOR HIS MAMA.

398
00:28:29,708 --> 00:28:34,844
PEOPLE TALK ABOUT
HOW ELVIS LET HIMSELF GO
THERE NEAR THE END,

399
00:28:34,913 --> 00:28:38,047
<i> HOW HE STOPPED CARING</i>
<i> ABOUT THE PEOPLE,</i>
<i> ABOUT THE MUSIC.</i>

400
00:28:39,183 --> 00:28:41,851
TO ME,
IT WAS JUST THE OPPOSITE.

401
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:44,821
THE OPPOSITE?
<i> YEAH.</i>

402
00:28:44,890 --> 00:28:46,890
HE CARED TOO MUCH.

403
00:28:48,593 --> 00:28:51,627
HE RAN SO FAST,

404
00:28:51,696 --> 00:28:53,963
SO QUICK,

405
00:28:54,032 --> 00:28:57,032
HE DIDN'T HAVE ANYTHING LEFT
TO FINISH THE RACE.

406
00:28:59,404 --> 00:29:02,338
TOO BAD I WON'T BE ABLE
TO FINISH IT FOR HIM.

407
00:29:04,509 --> 00:29:07,076
YOU NEVER KNOW, BERNIE.

408
00:29:07,145 --> 00:29:10,213
SOMETIMES A CHANGE OF SCENERY
CAN DO YOU GOOD.

409
00:29:14,018 --> 00:29:16,418
MAYBE.

410
00:29:19,157 --> 00:29:21,657
<i>[ Pager Beeping ]</i>

411
00:29:24,463 --> 00:29:26,463
[ Monitor Beeping ]

412
00:29:32,270 --> 00:29:34,437
IT'S OKAY, MAGGIE.

413
00:29:34,506 --> 00:29:36,806
YOU'RE NOT ALONE.

414
00:29:38,644 --> 00:29:41,645
[ Monitor: Sustained Tone ]

415
00:29:50,989 --> 00:29:52,989
<i> [ Monitor Clicks Off ]</i>

416
00:30:15,546 --> 00:30:17,480
IT'S A HUNDRED GRAND.

417
00:30:17,549 --> 00:30:20,950
- THAT WAS NOT THE ARRANGEMENT.
-<i> ACTUALLY, SYDNEY, IT WAS.</i>

418
00:30:29,928 --> 00:30:33,530
YOUR BOY IS IN
THE MARQUIS CASINO IN VEGAS.

419
00:30:33,598 --> 00:30:36,599
IT'S ALWAYS A PLEASURE
TAKING WHITE COLLAR
TO THE CLEANERS.

420
00:30:36,667 --> 00:30:39,135
<i> [ Miss Parker</i>
<i> Chuckles ]</i>

421
00:30:39,204 --> 00:30:41,137
I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

422
00:30:41,206 --> 00:30:44,307
I BROUGHT 200,000 WITH ME.
WHO KNEW YOU'D BE
SUCH A CHEAP DATE?

423
00:30:46,244 --> 00:30:49,211
COME ON, SYD.
WE'RE GOING TO LAS VEGAS,

424
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:52,281
A PLACE
WHERE MAYBE EVEN YOU
COULD GET LUCKY.

425
00:30:53,285 --> 00:30:55,217
[ Line Rings ]

426
00:30:55,287 --> 00:30:57,720
[ Woman ]
HOSPITAL ADMINISTRATION.
CAN YOU HOLD, PLEASE?

427
00:30:57,789 --> 00:31:00,290
<i> [ Jarod ]</i>
<i> UH, YES, I'LL HOLD.</i>

428
00:31:03,228 --> 00:31:08,164
YES, I WOULD LIKE TO ARRANGE
TO PAY MAGGIE BLAIRE'S
HOSPITAL BILLS.

429
00:31:08,233 --> 00:31:10,166
THEY HAVE?

430
00:31:10,235 --> 00:31:12,368
COULD YOU TELL ME
BY WHOM?

431
00:31:14,706 --> 00:31:16,706
THANK YOU.
[ Line Disconnects ]

432
00:31:41,566 --> 00:31:43,566
I THOUGHT
YOU'D COME.

433
00:31:46,004 --> 00:31:48,939
I WANTED
TO PAY MY RESPECTS.

434
00:31:49,007 --> 00:31:51,441
JUST LIKE YOU PAID
FOR MAGGIE'S
HOSPITAL BILLS...

435
00:31:51,509 --> 00:31:54,010
AND FOR THIS FUNERAL?

436
00:31:55,547 --> 00:31:58,080
YOU FOUND THE VIDEOTAPE,
DIDN'T YOU?

437
00:31:58,150 --> 00:32:00,082
WHAT?

438
00:32:00,152 --> 00:32:03,219
THE REAL SECURITY TAPE
FROM THE NIGHT
OF THE ATTACK.

439
00:32:03,288 --> 00:32:05,755
THE ONE
THAT PETER MADE SURE
THE POLICE NEVER SAW.

440
00:32:05,824 --> 00:32:08,624
IT SHOWS MAGGIE
LEAVING THE MARQUIS
WITH YOUR HUSBAND.

441
00:32:08,693 --> 00:32:12,395
THEY WERE HAVING AN AFFAIR,
WEREN'T THEY?
WHO ARE YOU?

442
00:32:12,464 --> 00:32:15,965
SOMEBODY WHO DOESN'T
BELIEVE THAT MAGGIE
DESERVED HER FATE.

443
00:32:16,033 --> 00:32:18,401
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

444
00:32:20,938 --> 00:32:24,206
YOU DON'T HAVE TO PRETEND
LIKE IT'S NOT HAPPENING ANYMORE.

445
00:32:28,213 --> 00:32:30,213
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

446
00:32:30,281 --> 00:32:32,281
HE DOESN'T MEAN TO HURT ME.

447
00:32:32,350 --> 00:32:34,483
YES, HE DOES.

448
00:32:34,552 --> 00:32:37,387
THIS IS YOUR HUSBAND'S
RAP SHEET.

449
00:32:37,455 --> 00:32:39,456
YOU'RE NOT THE FIRST PERSON
THAT HE'S HURT.

450
00:32:39,524 --> 00:32:44,127
AND UNLESS HE'S STOPPED,
MAGGIE'S NOT GONNA BE
THE LAST PERSON HE KILLS.

451
00:32:45,463 --> 00:32:47,464
MY GOD.

452
00:33:00,412 --> 00:33:03,813
KITTY... I'M HERE
BECAUSE I WANT TO HELP YOU.

453
00:33:07,919 --> 00:33:10,019
I CAN STOP HIM...

454
00:33:10,087 --> 00:33:12,021
IF YOU HELP ME.

455
00:33:12,090 --> 00:33:15,024
NO. NO, I--
I CAN'T DO THAT.

456
00:33:15,093 --> 00:33:19,195
WHEN I TOLD HIM
THAT MAGGIE WAS DEAD AND THAT
I KNEW WHAT HAD HAPPENED,

457
00:33:19,264 --> 00:33:21,197
H-HE LOST IT.

458
00:33:21,266 --> 00:33:23,967
HE SAID HE'D KILL ME
IF I TOLD ANYONE.

459
00:33:24,035 --> 00:33:28,104
AND THEN HE JUST HIT ME
AGAIN... AND AGAIN--

460
00:33:28,173 --> 00:33:30,774
[ Sobbing ]
AND AGAIN.

461
00:33:32,878 --> 00:33:34,977
WHY DID HE STOP?

462
00:33:36,081 --> 00:33:38,081
THE PHONE RANG.

463
00:33:39,518 --> 00:33:42,952
KITTY, ONE DAY
THE PHONE'S NOT GONNA RING.

464
00:35:14,512 --> 00:35:16,445
MR. HANLON.

465
00:35:16,514 --> 00:35:18,948
JAROD FELSON.

466
00:35:19,017 --> 00:35:20,950
I'VE DISCOVERED
A SERIOUS PROBLEM,

467
00:35:21,019 --> 00:35:23,953
AND I'D LIKE
TO DISCUSS IT WITH YOU
ONE-ON-ONE.

468
00:35:24,022 --> 00:35:26,856
SAY TOMORROW MORNING,
AROUND 10:00?

469
00:35:32,497 --> 00:35:35,331
IVY, IT'S MR. FELSON.

470
00:35:36,467 --> 00:35:39,468
I WAS WONDERING IF YOU
COULD DO ME A FAVOR.

471
00:35:43,541 --> 00:35:46,542
[ Speaking German ]

472
00:35:51,482 --> 00:35:53,416
HELLO?
PETER.

473
00:35:53,485 --> 00:35:55,418
JAROD FELSON.

474
00:35:55,486 --> 00:35:57,419
JAROD. WHAT'S UP?

475
00:35:57,489 --> 00:36:01,023
I'VE DISCOVERED
AN EVEN LARGER PROBLEM
THAN BEFORE.

476
00:36:01,092 --> 00:36:03,693
- IS IT DAVIS AGAIN?
- NO.

477
00:36:03,762 --> 00:36:06,295
BUT IT'S BIG,
SOMETHING YOU NEED TO HANDLE...

478
00:36:06,364 --> 00:36:08,130
PERSONALLY.

479
00:36:08,199 --> 00:36:11,166
CAN YOU MEET ME
TOMORROW MORNING,
AROUND 10:00?

480
00:36:11,235 --> 00:36:13,803
ABSOLUTELY.

481
00:36:13,872 --> 00:36:15,871
I'LL SEE YOU THERE.

482
00:36:32,023 --> 00:36:34,457
SO, WHAT ARE YOU,
ABOUT A 38?

483
00:36:34,525 --> 00:36:37,093
WHAT?
WAIST.

484
00:36:37,161 --> 00:36:39,261
UH, 30-- 36.

485
00:36:48,139 --> 00:36:51,073
<i> SEÑOR</i> JAROD,
FIVE NIGHTS
AND YOU DON'T SLEEP.

486
00:36:51,142 --> 00:36:53,075
[ Chuckles ]
HMM?

487
00:36:53,144 --> 00:36:56,145
TOO MUCH TO DO, BLANCA.
NOT ENOUGH HOURS IN THE DAY.

488
00:36:57,815 --> 00:36:59,582
JORGE!

489
00:36:59,651 --> 00:37:01,917
<i>¿HAS LEÍDO ESTE LIBRO?</i>
<i> SI.</i>

490
00:37:01,986 --> 00:37:04,887
<i> MUCHO.</i>
<i> TENGO CINCO NIÑOS.</i>

491
00:37:04,956 --> 00:37:07,022
<i>¡BLANCA, PERFECTO!</i>

492
00:37:07,091 --> 00:37:10,693
<i>¿QUIÉN ES EL HOMBRE</i>
<i>EN EL SOMBRERO AMARILLO?</i>

493
00:37:10,762 --> 00:37:12,995
MMM.
<i> NO SÉ, SEÑOR.</i>

494
00:37:13,064 --> 00:37:15,297
<i> NO SÉ.</i>
[ Sighs ]
<i>GRACIAS.</i>

495
00:37:17,234 --> 00:37:19,168
¿BLANCA?

496
00:37:19,237 --> 00:37:21,237
<i> ¿SÍ?</i>

497
00:37:22,507 --> 00:37:24,841
WOULD YOU DO ME A FAVOR?

498
00:37:24,909 --> 00:37:27,843
PETER, COME ON.
WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME.
WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?

499
00:37:27,913 --> 00:37:32,014
IT'S ABOUT A HUNDRED GRAND
WALKING OUT OF THIS CASINO
RIGHT UNDER YOUR VERY NOSE.

500
00:37:34,852 --> 00:37:36,786
<i>MR. HANLON!</i>
<i>FROM JAROD FELSON.</i>

501
00:37:36,854 --> 00:37:40,856
HE SAID HE'D MEET YOU
IN THE SECURITY BAY
AS SOON AS HE CAN.

502
00:37:40,925 --> 00:37:44,460
<i> [ Jarod ] SOMEBODY</i>
<i> HAS BEEN DOUBLE-COUNTING</i>
<i> THE CASH OUTLAYS.</i>

503
00:37:44,528 --> 00:37:47,463
BASED ON MY FINDINGS,
OVER A HUNDRED GRAND
IS BEING SKIMMED OFF THE TOP...

504
00:37:47,532 --> 00:37:49,398
EVERY TUESDAY
CASH PICKUP.

505
00:37:49,467 --> 00:37:52,134
YOU THINK DAVIS
WAS BEHIND THIS?
I'M NOT SURE.

506
00:37:52,203 --> 00:37:54,269
BUT IT'S BIGGER
THAN ONE GUY.

507
00:37:54,338 --> 00:37:57,273
AN ACCOUNTING SCAM
TIED INTO
THE ARMORED CAR COURIER.

508
00:37:57,342 --> 00:38:00,576
FOR EVERY $300,000
THAT'S DEPOSITED ON PAPER,

509
00:38:00,645 --> 00:38:04,413
ANOTHER HUNDRED GRAND
IS BEING DROPPED OFF
AT A SECOND LOCALE.

510
00:38:04,482 --> 00:38:06,415
BUT IF WE KEEP
THIS SCAM GOING,

511
00:38:06,484 --> 00:38:08,417
WE FIND OUT
WHERE THE LOCALE IS,

512
00:38:08,486 --> 00:38:11,487
WE CAN BRING DOWN
EVERYBODY THAT'S BEEN
RIPPING OFF THE MARQUIS.

513
00:38:11,555 --> 00:38:14,223
WHY DON'T WE JUST
BRING IN THE COPS?

514
00:38:14,292 --> 00:38:16,225
PETER,
THINK ABOUT THIS.

515
00:38:16,294 --> 00:38:18,227
IF YOU PULL THIS OFF,

516
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:21,397
YOU ARE GONNA BE
STEVE HANLON'S
$20 MILLION HERO.

517
00:38:31,509 --> 00:38:34,210
THE MARQUIS. NOW.
YES, MA'AM.

518
00:38:45,890 --> 00:38:49,324
WHY ME?
I'M THE NEW FACE AROUND HERE.
NOBODY'S GONNA TRUST ME.

519
00:38:49,394 --> 00:38:52,995
BUT IF THEIR COURIER
IS GREETED BY
THE PRESIDENT OF THE CASINO,

520
00:38:53,064 --> 00:38:55,697
HE'S GONNA PLAY
RIGHT INTO YOUR HANDS.

521
00:39:00,604 --> 00:39:02,605
IT'S SHOWTIME.

522
00:39:12,550 --> 00:39:14,483
WHERE'S MR. DAVIS?

523
00:39:14,552 --> 00:39:17,486
[ Clears Throat ]
MR. DAVIS WORKED FOR ME
IN MORE WAYS THAN ONE.

524
00:39:17,555 --> 00:39:20,489
I'M PETER MORGAN.
I RUN THE MARQUIS.

525
00:39:20,558 --> 00:39:22,991
IT'S BUSINESS AS USUAL.
YOU UNDERSTAND?

526
00:39:23,060 --> 00:39:26,362
SURE.
BUSINESS AS USUAL.

527
00:39:26,431 --> 00:39:29,364
TAKE THE SKIM TO THE DROP.
DEPOSIT THE REST IN THE BANK.

528
00:39:29,434 --> 00:39:31,566
WE'LL SEE YOU
NEXT TUESDAY.
OKAY.

529
00:39:42,079 --> 00:39:44,414
[ Imitates Elvis Presley ]
WELL, THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

530
00:39:52,323 --> 00:39:54,256
THAT WAS EXCITING!

531
00:39:54,325 --> 00:39:56,258
GUY FELL FOR
EVERYTHING I SAID.

532
00:39:56,327 --> 00:39:58,493
HE MUST BE A COMPLETE IDIOT.

533
00:40:01,632 --> 00:40:03,566
[ Sighs ]

534
00:40:03,634 --> 00:40:05,935
FIND HIM.

535
00:40:06,003 --> 00:40:08,103
[ Chuckling ]

536
00:40:08,172 --> 00:40:10,206
<i> [ Morgan ]</i>
<i> STEVE!</i>

537
00:40:10,274 --> 00:40:13,176
- I DIDN'T THINK YOU'D BE HERE.
- SURPRISE.

538
00:40:13,244 --> 00:40:16,745
- YOU WON'T BELIEVE
WHAT I'VE BEEN DOING.
- BET ME.

539
00:40:17,749 --> 00:40:19,681
BUSINESS AS USUAL.

540
00:40:19,751 --> 00:40:24,287
TAKE THE SKIM TO THE DROP.
DEPOSIT THE REST IN THE BANK.
WE'LL SEE YOU NEXT TUESDAY.

541
00:40:24,355 --> 00:40:26,222
<i>[ Bernie ]</i>
<i>OKAY.</i>

542
00:40:28,826 --> 00:40:32,061
STEVE, I WASN'T REALLY
TAKING THE MONEY. WE WERE--

543
00:40:32,130 --> 00:40:34,296
THERE'S A GREAT DEAL
OF UNREPORTED CASH
LEAVING THIS CASINO.

544
00:40:34,365 --> 00:40:36,199
I KNOW!
AND, UH, WE WERE--

545
00:40:36,267 --> 00:40:39,468
AND A GREAT DEAL OF CASH
IS GOING IN YOUR
SWISS BANK ACCOUNT.

546
00:40:39,537 --> 00:40:42,638
- I DON'T HAVE A SWISS ACCOUNT.
- OH.

547
00:40:48,846 --> 00:40:50,913
<i>ELECTRONIC TRANSFERS...</i>

548
00:40:50,982 --> 00:40:53,549
FOR $4.6 MILLION.

549
00:40:55,219 --> 00:40:57,653
THAT IS YOUR SIGNATURE,
ISN'T IT?

550
00:41:06,630 --> 00:41:08,097
I DIDN'T DO THIS.

551
00:41:08,165 --> 00:41:10,332
TELL HIM.
TELL HIM THE TRUTH.

552
00:41:10,401 --> 00:41:12,167
I AM SORRY, MR. HANLON.

553
00:41:12,236 --> 00:41:14,803
I'M SORRY
I DIDN'T CATCH THIS SOONER.

554
00:41:14,872 --> 00:41:18,307
<i>AND THE FIGURE IS CLOSER</i>
<i>TO 4.8.</i>

555
00:41:20,478 --> 00:41:23,579
EVERY INSTINCT IN MY GUT
TOLD ME YOU WERE BAD NEWS.

556
00:41:26,517 --> 00:41:28,817
STEVE, I DIDN'T DO
ANYTHING WRONG--

557
00:41:28,886 --> 00:41:32,455
[ Groans, Panting ]

558
00:41:32,523 --> 00:41:35,157
FELSON, DAMN IT!

559
00:41:35,226 --> 00:41:36,825
<i>I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.</i>

560
00:41:36,894 --> 00:41:38,827
I DIDN'T DO
ANYTHING WRONG.

561
00:41:41,065 --> 00:41:43,999
NEITHER DID MAGGIE BLAIRE.

562
00:41:52,209 --> 00:41:54,142
<i> DETECTIVE BENSON,</i>
<i> HOMICIDE.</i>

563
00:41:54,212 --> 00:41:57,279
I'M LOOKING FOR
A PETER MORGAN.
HE'S IN A MEETING RIGHT NOW.

564
00:41:57,348 --> 00:41:59,281
<i> [ Thud, Crash ]</i>

565
00:41:59,350 --> 00:42:01,983
I THINK HE'S ASKING
FOR A RAISE.

566
00:42:02,052 --> 00:42:04,053
<i>[ Blow Lands ]</i>

567
00:42:10,628 --> 00:42:12,961
♪♪ [ Whistling ]
[ Snapping Fingers ]

568
00:42:14,532 --> 00:42:16,798
[ Bell Rings ]

569
00:42:16,867 --> 00:42:18,800
<i>[ Coins Falling Into Tray ]</i>

570
00:42:18,869 --> 00:42:20,802
♪♪ [ Continues Whistling ]

571
00:42:20,871 --> 00:42:23,138
♪♪ [ Slows, Stops ]

572
00:42:23,207 --> 00:42:25,207
JAROD!

573
00:42:30,548 --> 00:42:32,981
TAKE THE REAR!

574
00:43:00,577 --> 00:43:03,512
JAROD!
DON'T RUN! PLEASE!

575
00:43:03,581 --> 00:43:05,847
THERE'S NOWHERE TO GO.

576
00:43:05,916 --> 00:43:08,049
<i>[ Man On Radio ]</i>
<i>SECURITY ALERT. POOL AREA.</i>

577
00:43:08,118 --> 00:43:10,619
MY LUCKY DAY!

578
00:43:10,687 --> 00:43:12,454
<i>[ Approaching Footsteps</i>
<i>  Running ]</i>

579
00:43:12,523 --> 00:43:15,691
<i> WE GOT YOUR RADIO CALL,</i>
<i> MR. FELSON.</i>
<i> IS THERE A PROBLEM?</i>

580
00:43:17,862 --> 00:43:19,695
YES, THERE IS.

581
00:43:19,763 --> 00:43:22,598
A COUPLE OF GRIFTERS
TRYING A ROULETTE SCAM.

582
00:43:22,666 --> 00:43:26,068
<i> CALL THE L.V.P.D.</i>
<i> AND HAVE THEM PICKED UP.</i>

583
00:43:27,204 --> 00:43:29,138
LET GO OF ME.

584
00:43:29,206 --> 00:43:32,808
YOU MIGHT WANT TO
STRIP-SEARCH THIS ONE.
SHE COULD BE PALMING CHIPS.

585
00:43:32,876 --> 00:43:34,810
OH, YOU BASTARD!

586
00:43:34,878 --> 00:43:36,812
I'M JUST DOING MY JOB,
MA'AM.

587
00:43:36,881 --> 00:43:38,881
HEAD OF SECURITY, YOU KNOW.

588
00:43:39,951 --> 00:43:42,551
- I WILL GET YOU.
- YOU WANNA BET?

589
00:43:43,721 --> 00:43:45,287
<i> TAILS.</i>

590
00:43:46,857 --> 00:43:48,724
COME ON, LADY.

591
00:44:35,506 --> 00:44:38,874
<i>NOT A PAPER CLIP.</i>
<i>NO TRASH, NO LINT.</i>

592
00:44:40,010 --> 00:44:42,011
NOTHING BUT THIS.

593
00:44:43,114 --> 00:44:45,114
AND THE USUAL.

594
00:44:49,653 --> 00:44:51,587
<i> SEÑOR</i> SYDNEY?

595
00:44:51,655 --> 00:44:54,323
<i>DÍGAME.</i>
<i> PARA USTED.</i>

596
00:45:00,564 --> 00:45:03,232
"TO THE MAN
IN THE YELLOW HAT.

597
00:45:03,300 --> 00:45:05,801
FROM THE MONKEY
WHO GOT AWAY."

598
00:45:16,013 --> 00:45:18,013
ALL RIGHT.
[ Chuckles ]

599
00:45:22,085 --> 00:45:26,021
YOU'RE REALLY GONNA RELEASE
HIM BACK INTO THE WILD?
THAT'S THE PLAN.

600
00:45:26,089 --> 00:45:29,024
LIVING CREATURES,
THEY DON'T BELONG
IN CAPTIVITY.

601
00:45:29,092 --> 00:45:31,093
[ Hooting Quietly ]

602
00:45:34,465 --> 00:45:36,431
[ Chuckles ]

603
00:46:11,335 --> 00:46:12,334
[ Mews ]

